<h1>Living in the Trail Area</h1>
<p>You know that Trail is a great place to live, work, play and raise a family. Our program offers advice, information and supplies to keep your home environment healthy and safe. &nbsp;</p>
<p>Keep reading if you are planning a home renovation, construction, excavation or demolition project or if you&rsquo;re interested in our yard and garden soil program.&nbsp; For more information on keeping your family healthy and safe, see <a href="/parents/">I&rsquo;m a Parent</a>. <br /><br />Our <a href="/pages/homeandgarden">Home &amp; Garden Program</a>&nbsp;offers free health and safety advice, supplies, and equipment use to homeowners and tenants doing home renovations in Trail or Rivervale. The same support is available for renovation of pre-1976 homes throughout Greater Trail. <a title="Contact Us" href="/pages/contact/">Contact us</a> on weekdays for free safety supplies. Contractors are advised to use our <a href="/upload/resources/8/THEP_brochure_HRSP_proof_final3_original.pdf">lead-safe renovation guidelines</a> for all residential projects in Trail and Rivervale and pre-1976 homes in Greater Trail.&nbsp; Our goal is for all home renovators to use our program.<br /><br />The <a href="/pages/homeandgarden">Home &amp; Garden Program</a> offers soil testing for people with vegetable gardens, families with young children, and pregnant women in Trail and Rivervale. If you have questions about metals in soil or local produce, check out &ldquo;What do I need to know about soil&rdquo; in the <a href="/pages/homeandgarden">Fact Sheet</a>, the questions about soil in the <a title="FAQ" href="/pages/faq">FAQ</a>, &nbsp;or <a title="Contact Us" href="/pages/contact/">contact</a> our Community Program Office. We&rsquo;re here to answer your questions.<br /><br /></p>